50|$|Clutch delay valves {{operate as}} <b>one-way</b> <b>restrictor</b> valves that limit {{the volume of}} fluid that can move through the lines in a given time. This ensures a steady quick and firm {{engagement}} without being too fast for the drive train to handle since clutches can quickly disengage but re-engagement is damped. The clutch delay valve slows clutch engagement and was intended to reduce drivetrain shock {{in the event that}} an inexperienced driver quickly engaged the clutch at higher revs.|$|E

